  "text": "Our interest for the existence of quasi-isometrically embedded free subsemigroups comes from the following result of Bourgain [CITATION_1] : a regular tree of degree at least three has no quasi-isometric embedding into a Hilbert space (nor into any uniformly convex Banach space); note that a free semigroup is quasi-isometric to such a tree.",
